\p
\v 7 And these are the sons of Benjamin; Sallu the son of MeshuUam, the son of Joed, the son of Pedaiah, the son of Kolaiah, the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ithiel, the son of Jesaiah.
\p
\v 8 And after him Gabbai, Sallai, nine hundred twenty and eight.
\p
\v 9 And Joel the son of Zichri was their overseer: and Judah the son of Senuah was second over the city.
\p
\v 10 Of the priests: Jedaiah the son of Joiarib, Jachin.
\p
\v 11 Seraiah the son of Hilkiah, the son of MeshuUam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, was the ruler of the house of God.
\p
\v 13 And their brethren that did the work of the house were eight hundred twenty and two: and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pelaliah, the son of Amzi, the son of Zechariah, the son of Pashur, the son of Malchiah,
\p
\v 13 And his brethren, chief of the fathers, two hundred forty and two: and Amashai the son of Azareel, the son of Ahasai, the son of Meshillemoth, the son of Immer,
\p
\v 14 And their brethren, mighty men of valour, an hundred twenty and eight: and their overseer was Zabdiel, the son of one of the great men.
\p
\v 15 Also of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hashub, the son of - Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Bunni;
\p
\v 16 And Shabbethai and Jozabad, of the chief of the Levites, had the oversight of the outward business of the house of God.
\p
\v 17 And Mattaniah the son of Micha, the son of Zabdi, the son of Asaph, was the principal to begin the thanksgiving in prayer: and Bakbukiah the second among his brethren, and Abda the son of Shammua, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun.
\p
\v 18 All the Levites in the holy city were two hundred fourscore and four.
\p
\v 19 Moreover the porters, Akkub, Talmon, and their brethren that kept the gates, were an hundred seventy and two.
\p
\v 20 And the residue of Israel, of the priests, and the Levites, were in all the cities of Judah, every one in his inheritance.
\p
\v 21 But the Nethinims dwelt in Ophel: and Ziha and Gispa were over the Nethinims.
\p
